<subSubSection box="[178,582,1166,1193]" pageId="5" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="5.[178,582,1166,1193]" box="[178,582,1166,1193]" pageId="5">
<heading box="[178,582,1166,1193]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="5" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(Gervais, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[178,582,1166,1193]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insigne">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,405,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5">Agriotherium insigne</emphasis>
(Gervais, 1859)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,647,1223,1406]" pageId="5">
MATERIAL EXAMINED. — Fragment of a left maxilla with the alveolus of the first three premolars, the complete upper carnassial and an anterior fragment of the M1 (
<collectionCode box="[121,206,1303,1327]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="5">MNHN</collectionCode>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="GERVAIS P." box="[227,363,1302,1327]" pageId="5" pagination="147 - 168" refId="ref16212" refString="GERVAIS P. 1853. - Description des ossements fossiles de mammiferes rapportes d'Espagne par MM. de Verneuil, Collomb et de Loriere. Bulletin de la Societe geologique de France 2 e ser., 10: 147 - 168, pls 3 - 6." type="journal article" year="1853">Gervais 1853</bibRefCitation>
: pl. IV, fig. 3; 1859a: pl. 81, fig. 2). Unfortunately, the original specimen, as well as other materials from the Alcoy mine, are lost. We could study a cast deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[395,481,1382,1405]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="5">MNHN</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,539,1430,1454]" box="[113,539,1430,1454]" pageId="5">
MEASUREMENTS. — See Appendix: 
<tableCitation box="[461,539,1430,1454]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="30.[113,122,288,305]" captionText="TABLE 1. — Measurements (in mm) of the upper carnassial (P4) of Agriotherium from Alcoy (cast MNHN), compared with the homologous element of A. insigne (Gervais, 1869) from Montpellier (Gervais 1859a), A. roblesi Morales &amp; Aguirre, 1976 from Venta del Moro (MGUV), A. palaeoindicum (Lydekker, 1884) and A. sivalense (Falconer &amp; Cautley, 1836) (Lydekker 1884), A. intermedium Qiu &amp; Schmidt-Kittler, 1983 (Qiu &amp; Schmidt-Kittler 1983) and A. africanum Hendey, 1972 (Hendey 1980). Abbreviations: DAP, antero-posterior diameter; DT, transverse diameter." pageId="5">Table 1.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,647,1484,1700]" box="[113,258,1484,1510]" pageId="5">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,647,1484,1700]" lastBlockId="5.[677,1210,216,305]" pageId="5">The P4 is the only complete tooth preserved in the maxilla. It is a robust tooth, with a very well developed parastyle that shows a single internal edge continued in the lingual cingulum. The protocone is simple and consists of a backwards directed conical cusp, surrounded by a well marked basal cingulum. At the base of the metastyle is a strong lingual cingulum and another weaker one in the labial side.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" pageId="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[677,1210,343,1699]" box="[677,806,343,369]" pageId="5">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[677,1210,343,1699]" pageId="5">
The upper carnassial from Alcoy shows a morphology that can be considered typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1837" box="[1065,1203,406,432]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1203,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="5">Agriotherium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus present in Europe from the latest Miocene (MN13) of Venta del Moro (
<bibRefCitation author="MORALES J. &amp; AGUIRRE E." pageId="5" pagination="31 - 82" refId="ref17723" refString="MORALES J. &amp; AGUIRRE E. 1976. - Carnivoros de Venta del Moro. Trabajos sobre Neogeno-Cuaternario 5: 31 - 82." type="journal article" year="1976">Morales &amp; Aguirre 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MORALES J." box="[752,912,501,527]" pageId="5" refId="ref17690" refString="MORALES J. 1984. - Venta del Moro: su macrofauna de mamiferos y biostratigrafia continental del Mioceno terminal mediterraneo. Editorial de la Universidad Complutense, Madrid, 340 p." type="book" year="1984">Morales 1984</bibRefCitation>
) until the upper Pliocene (MN16) of Vialette (
<bibRefCitation author="HELBING H." box="[904,1061,533,559]" pageId="5" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref16723" refString="HELBING H. 1932. - Uber einen Indarctos - Schadel aus dem Pontien der Insel Samos. Nebst einen Anhang: Hyaenarctos spec. aus dem Pliocaen von Vialette (Haute- Loire). Memoires de la Societe paleontologique de Suisse 52: 1 - 18, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1932">Helbing 1932</bibRefCitation>
). When comparing with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Weithofer, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Weithofer" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[809,1182,564,590]" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Indarctos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atticus">
<emphasis box="[809,977,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="5">Indarctos atticus</emphasis>
(Weithofer, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
, it can be noticed that the P4 of this species generally presents a less developed parastyle, even relatively very reduced in some specimens from Concud (
<bibRefCitation author="CRUSAFONT M." box="[683,852,691,717]" pageId="5" pagination="177 - 184" refId="ref15574" refString="CRUSAFONT M. 1962. - Indarctos atticus, un nuevo carnivoro del Pikermiense espanol. Teruel 27: 177 - 184, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1962">Crusafont 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MONTOYA P. &amp; ALCALA L. &amp; MORALES J." box="[860,1071,691,718]" pageId="5" pagination="123 - 151" refId="ref17653" refString="MONTOYA P., ALCALA L. &amp; MORALES J. 2001. - Indarctos (Ursidae, Mammalia) from the Spanish Turolian (Upper Miocene). Scripta Geologica 122: 123 - 151." type="journal article" year="2001">
Montoya 
<emphasis box="[961,1009,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, this parastyle shows two edges (lingual and labial) in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weithofer" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[708,884,754,780]" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Indarctos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atticus">
<emphasis box="[708,884,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="5">Indarctos atticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the specimen from Alcoy only shows a lingual edge, a typical characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Petter &amp; Thomas 1986)" baseAuthorityName="Petter &amp; Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[787,1206,818,845]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,925,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="5">Agriotherium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PETTER G. &amp; THOMAS H." box="[940,1198,818,845]" pageId="5" pagination="573 - 586" refId="ref17918" refString="PETTER G. &amp; THOMAS H. 1986. - Les Agriotheriinae (Mammalia, Carnivora) neogenes de l'Ancien Monde. Presence du genre Indarctos dans la faune de Menacer (ex-Marceau), Algerie. Geobios 19 (5): 573 - 586." type="journal article" year="1986">Petter &amp; Thomas 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover and in contrast to the studied specimen, the protocone in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weithofer" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[860,950,882,907]" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Indarctos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atticus">
<emphasis box="[860,950,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="5">I. atticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly always more or less bifurcated (
<bibRefCitation author="MONTOYA P. &amp; ALCALA L. &amp; MORALES J." box="[843,1068,913,939]" pageId="5" pagination="123 - 151" refId="ref17653" refString="MONTOYA P., ALCALA L. &amp; MORALES J. 2001. - Indarctos (Ursidae, Mammalia) from the Spanish Turolian (Upper Miocene). Scripta Geologica 122: 123 - 151." type="journal article" year="2001">
Montoya 
<emphasis box="[950,994,913,939]" italics="true" pageId="5">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[677,1210,343,1699]" pageId="5">
The general morphology of the P4 studied in this work is very similar to that of the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lydekker, 1884)" baseAuthorityName="Lydekker" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[707,1077,1008,1034]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palaeindicum">
<emphasis box="[707,880,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. palaeindicum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LYDEKKER R." box="[895,1069,1008,1034]" pageId="5" pagination="178 - 363" refId="ref17033" refString="LYDEKKER R. 1884. - Siwalik and Narbada Carnivora. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India, Palaeontologia Indica ser. X, vol. II, part 6: 178 - 363, pls 26 - 45." type="journal article" year="1884">Lydekker, 1884</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Falconer &amp; Cautley, 1836)" authorityName="Lydekker" authorityYear="1884" baseAuthorityName="Falconer &amp; Cautley" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sivalense">
<emphasis box="[1090,1210,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. sivalense</emphasis>
(Falconer &amp; Cautley, 1836)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1026,1127,1040,1066]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insigne">
<emphasis box="[1026,1127,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. insigne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="GERVAIS P." box="[707,871,1071,1098]" pageId="5" refId="ref16260" refString="GERVAIS P. 1859 a. - Zoologie et paleontologie francaises. 2 e ed. Arthus Bertrand, Paris, 544 p., 84 pls." type="book" year="1859">Gervais (1859a</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 81), 
<bibRefCitation author="LYDEKKER R." box="[960,1130,1071,1097]" pageId="5" pagination="178 - 363" refId="ref17033" refString="LYDEKKER R. 1884. - Siwalik and Narbada Carnivora. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India, Palaeontologia Indica ser. X, vol. II, part 6: 178 - 363, pls 26 - 45." type="journal article" year="1884">Lydekker (1884</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 30) and 
<bibRefCitation author="FRICK C." box="[723,860,1103,1130]" pageId="5" pagination="1 - 119" refId="ref16154" refString="FRICK C. 1926. - The Hemicyoninae and an American Tertiary bear. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 56: 1 - 119." type="journal article" year="1926">Frick (1926)</bibRefCitation>
, and also to most P4 of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendey, 1972" authorityName="Hendey" authorityYear="1972" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5">A. africanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="HENDEY Q. B." box="[732,886,1134,1161]" pageId="5" pagination="115 - 132" refId="ref16817" refString="HENDEY Q. B. 1972. - A Pliocene ursid from South Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 59 (6): 115 - 132, 2 pls." type="journal article" year="1972">Hendey, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(described by 
<bibRefCitation author="HENDEY Q. B." box="[1045,1205,1134,1161]" pageId="5" pagination="115 - 132" refId="ref16817" refString="HENDEY Q. B. 1972. - A Pliocene ursid from South Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 59 (6): 115 - 132, 2 pls." type="journal article" year="1972">Hendey (1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="HENDEY Q. B." box="[677,737,1166,1192]" pageId="5" pagination="1 - 109" refId="ref16850" refString="HENDEY Q. B. 1980. - Agriotherium (Mammalia, Ursidae) from Langebaanweg, South Africa, and relationships of the genus. Annals of the South African Museum 81 (1): 1 - 109." type="journal article" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
). Its size falls within the range of the minimal values of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendey" authorityYear="1972" box="[827,966,1198,1224]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis box="[827,966,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[677,778,1230,1256]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insigne">
<emphasis box="[677,778,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. insigne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker" authorityYear="1884" baseAuthorityName="Falconer &amp; Cautley" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[829,945,1229,1256]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sivalense">
<emphasis box="[829,945,1229,1256]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. sivalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it is clearly far from a non-published tooth of 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales &amp; Aguirre, 1976" authorityName="Morales &amp; Aguirre" authorityYear="1976" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roblesi">
<emphasis box="[999,1092,1261,1288]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. roblesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MORALES J. &amp; AGUIRRE E." pageId="5" pagination="31 - 82" refId="ref17723" refString="MORALES J. &amp; AGUIRRE E. 1976. - Carnivoros de Venta del Moro. Trabajos sobre Neogeno-Cuaternario 5: 31 - 82." type="journal article" year="1976">Morales &amp; Aguirre, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the latest Miocene (MN13) of Venta del Moro, which is a much larger and more robust tooth with a less individualized protocone. It also differs largely from 
<taxonomicName authority="Stach, 1957" authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1957" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedium">
<emphasis box="[968,1135,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="5">A. intermedium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="STACH J." pageId="5" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref18199" refString="STACH J. 1957. - Agriotherium intermedium n. sp. from the Pliocene bone breccia of Weze. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica 2 (1): 1 - 17, 2 pls." type="journal article" year="1957">Stach, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the lower Pliocene of Weze (
<bibRefCitation author="STACH J." box="[1082,1202,1419,1446]" pageId="5" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref18199" refString="STACH J. 1957. - Agriotherium intermedium n. sp. from the Pliocene bone breccia of Weze. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica 2 (1): 1 - 17, 2 pls." type="journal article" year="1957">Stach 1957</bibRefCitation>
) and of Xiaoxian (Qiu &amp; Schmidt-Kittler 1983), a relatively small 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Petter &amp; Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[843,981,1483,1509]" class="Mammalia" family="Agriochoeridae" genus="Agriotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[843,981,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="5">Agriotherium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[995,1077,1483,1509]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="30.[113,122,288,305]" captionText="TABLE 1. — Measurements (in mm) of the upper carnassial (P4) of Agriotherium from Alcoy (cast MNHN), compared with the homologous element of A. insigne (Gervais, 1869) from Montpellier (Gervais 1859a), A. roblesi Morales &amp; Aguirre, 1976 from Venta del Moro (MGUV), A. palaeoindicum (Lydekker, 1884) and A. sivalense (Falconer &amp; Cautley, 1836) (Lydekker 1884), A. intermedium Qiu &amp; Schmidt-Kittler, 1983 (Qiu &amp; Schmidt-Kittler 1983) and A. africanum Hendey, 1972 (Hendey 1980). Abbreviations: DAP, antero-posterior diameter; DT, transverse diameter." pageId="5">Table 1</tableCitation>
; 
